musb: host - fall back to PIO when the RX DMA backend declines a transfer

In musb_host_rx(), when musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41() returns false the
helper has already released hw_ep->rx_channel, but the caller's local `dma`
still points at the old channel, so the following `if (!dma)` PIO block is
skipped and the received packet is silently dropped -- the URB never completes.

This never bites inventra/ux500 because those DMA every host IN transfer. The
sunxi_dma backend, however, gates short/misaligned transfers to PIO (its
channel_program() returns 0), which exposes the missing fallback: the AA
protocol's small IN responses (e.g. 12 bytes) were lost and the session stalled
right after "Accessory linked". Refresh the local `dma` (now NULL) so the RX
falls through to PIO, mirroring the existing TX PIO fallback in
musb_tx_dma_program().

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
@@ -1924,8 +1924,14 @@
 			if (musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41(c, hw_ep, qh, urb,
 							   xfer_len, iso_err))
 				goto finish;
-			else
-				dev_err(musb->controller, "error: rx_dma failed\n");
+			/*
+			 * The DMA backend declined this RX (e.g. a short
+			 * transfer the sunxi engine rejects): the helper has
+			 * already released rx_channel, so drop our stale local
+			 * ref and fall through to the PIO path below instead of
+			 * losing the packet.  Mirrors the TX PIO fallback.
+			 */
+			dma = hw_ep->rx_channel;
 		}
 
 		if (!dma) {
